{
  "stem": "15174.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I was playing with them and kids just pick up a language rapidly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was a-- I told you there were about 200 people living in this village.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was a one-room schoolhouse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "All grades were in this one room, and there was one teacher who just taught all the grades.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember it very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I remember exactly where I sat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I remember there was a bookcase in the back which was called library.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I remember the-- the name of the teacher, Madame [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Picquel, ?] and she was terrific.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Her-- She was there with her husband.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They had also fled from Northern France I believe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Her husband taught school in a village nearby.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They had escaped because the rumor was that they were communists, and of course, the Nazi's were looking for communists, also, to kill them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Anyway, after we got back to the village, I have some very pleasant memories of that stay in France.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The people generally were very nice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Although, I have to say that I don't know when, but soon after we arrived, some anti-Semitism began to be felt.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I mean I remember one kid in particular who would say 'dirty Jew' and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And that-- they didn't know anything about this before because there were no Jews in this town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't know what a Jew-- The only thing they knew about Jews was what they had read in the Bible.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we told them we were Jewish, they stared at us, 'what do you mean you're Jewish?' I mean they had this conception that Jews had horns or something.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Really.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean I'm not kidding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they couldn't-- they couldn't fathom the fact that we were Jews and that we looked just like anybody else.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
